SYNOPSIS
========
   object master(             )
   object master(intÂ dont_load)

DESCRIPTION
===========
   Returns the master object.

   If dont_load(E) is false, the function first makes sure that the master 
   object exists.

   If dont_load(E) is true, the function just returns the current master 
   object, or 0 if the current master has been destructed.

HISTORY
=======
   - introduced (3.2.10)

SEE ALSO
========
   `overview`
